    {
      "paragraph_name": "1200-SCHEDULE-PSB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph simulates scheduling a PSB (Program Specification Block) in IMS. It simulates a DLI SCHD call using a DISPLAY statement and reads a record from MOCK-FILE, moving the value of MOCK-ALPHA-STATUS to DIBSTAT and IMS-RETURN-CODE. If PSB-SCHEDULED-MORE-THAN-ONCE is true, it simulates a DLI TERM call and another DLI SCHD call, reading mock data after each. If STATUS-OK is true, it sets IMS-PSB-SCHD to TRUE; otherwise, it sets error flags and calls 9500-LOG-ERROR to log the error. The paragraph uses mock data from MOCK-FILE to simulate IMS interactions and sets error codes based on simulated IMS responses.",
